com.camerontec.util.io

Class ByteArrayUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.util.io.ByteArrayUtils

  • public final class ByteArrayUtils
extends Object
    Utility methods for converting between native types and their big endian byte array representations.

    These utilities are considered low level and therefore are all unchecked. That is, all methods assume that byte[] parameters are both non null and of an appropriate length. It is the caller's responsibility to make sure these conditions are always met.

    Note: This class is being considered for deprecation. Prefer NativeTypeByteUtils instead.

      • getBoolean

        public static boolean getBoolean(byte[] array,
                                 int offset)
        Return a boolean value from a source byte array at the specified offset.

        Only a single byte at the specified offset if inspected. A true value is returned unless that byte is zero.

        Parameters:
        array - The source byte array.
        offset - The offset.
